The 18th World Beverage Innovation AwardsThe World Beverage Innovation Awards is a collaboration between FoodBev Media and the International Beer, Brewing and Beverage Industry Exhibition in Nuremberg, Germany.(Brau Beviale). It attracted 279 entries from 25 countries and 22 different categories. The finalists were announced on October 15 and the final winners will be announced on November 11Announced online (United Kingdom). We saw Yuanqi Forest 's LP28 sugar-free yoghurt shortlisted for Best Milk Drink, Ilyan Mushi' s "GOGO Wuhan" campaign shortlisted for Best Marketing Campaign, and PepsiCo and People 's Daily New Media' s packaging shortlisted for Best Packaging Design/Label. Laura Nettle, Senior Marketing Director, FoodBev Media, said:We are delighted to celebrate the 18th year of the annual World Beverage Innovation Awards with Brau Beviale. From new flavors, concepts and features to branding, packaging and manufacturing, we see trends in the beverage industry as the industry continues to innovate in a more sustainable way.100% recycled glass can be re-melted into new bottles. The water is bagged in boxes that are 100% recyclable, reducing packaging by 66% and reducing carbon emissions by 97%. LatCub is 100% biodegradable, uses less paper, and uses no environmentally harmful glues or tapes. The Ardagh Group has developed technology that re-melts 100% recycled glass into new bottles. The final winners will be announced on FoodBev Media 's YouTube channel on 11 November (United Kingdom), and FBIF will keep you posted!
